CDR2 is an onco-neural antigen and has been associated with cerebellar ataxia.
cerebellar degeneration-related protein 2
CDH18 (cadherin 18) is specifically expressed in the central nervous system.

EEF2K is a kinase involved in the regulation of protein synthesis elongation and has been recently associated with learning and memory, synaptic plasticity, and the short-term antidepressant action of ketamine. eef2k-knockout mice have been described to have defects in the reproductive system, and those carrying a homozygous-inactivating pathogenic variant leading to 0.5% residual activity showed learning memory deficits and altered brain activity.

Under normal physiological conditions, modulates its basal activity, preventing overactivation. Keeps control over reactive oxygen species (ROS) generation.

In stress conditions, the modulation of complex III by TRAP1 may support a shift in energy metabolism between oxidative phosphorylation and glycolysis
TRPM7 phosphorylates EEF2K on Ser77 (Ser78 in human)

EEF2K is a kinase involved in the regulation of protein synthesis elongation and has been recently associated with learning and memory, synaptic plasticity, and the short-term antidepressant action of ketamine. eef2k-knockout mice have been described to have defects in the reproductive system, and those carrying a homozygous-inactivating pathogenic variant leading to 0.5% residual activity showed learning memory deficits and altered brain activity.
Calmodulin (CaM)-dependent eukaryotic elongation factor 2 kinase.

Ubiquinol-Cytochrome C Reductase Core Protein 2
UQCRC2 is a fundamental protein for the assembly of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex.
site: Thr-53, Thr-56, Thr-58
EEF2K phosphorylates and inactivates EEF2
phosphorylates eEF2 at Thr56
Involved in mitochondrial respirasome assembly and multi-pass transmembrane protein insertion into ER membrane

Phosphorylation at Ser359 inhibits eef2k activity even at high calcium concentrations.inactivation of eef2k by cdc2 may serve to keep eef2 active during mitosis [mouse embryonic fibroblasts] [signor - https://signor.uniroma2.it/relation_result.php?id=O00418]

Phosphorylation of EEF2 at Ser595 is suggested to facilitate the recruitment of eEF2K, thereby promoting the phosphorylation of Thr56. This modification is identified as the first known regulatory mechanism of eEF2 that directly affects its phosphorylation by eEF2K. Given that eEF2K mediates all known regulatory modifications of eEF2, S595 phosphorylation is proposed to play a significant role in modulating elongation in response to various physiological conditions.

comments.content: Copy number variations in the region 16p12.2 (exact position on the chromosome: Chr16:21950135-22431889 (GRCh37), are rare, pathological mutations in the human genome. It is a risk variation for neuropsychiatric diseases like schizophrenia (Kirov et al. 2014, [10.1016/j.biopsych.2013.07.022](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.biopsych.2013.07.022))
